Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Certificate validation fails during authentication

Solution: Verify certificate includes correct SAN with UPN format
Check Extended Key Usage includes Client Authentication OID
Ensure certificate is signed by trusted CA
Issue: Enumeration script returns no results

Solution: Verify LDAP connectivity to domain controller
Check user permissions for reading certificate template objects
Confirm correct domain and credential parameters
Issue: PFX creation fails with OpenSSL errors

Solution: Ensure certificate and key files are in correct PEM format
Verify CA certificate is included in PFX bundle
Check file permissions and paths
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated Active Directory Certificate Services exploitation techniques using Certify and ForgeCert methodologies. Students learned to enumerate ADCS vulnerabilities, forge certificates for privilege escalation, and automate exploitation workflows. Understanding these attacks is critical for both offensive security assessments and defensive hardening of AD environments.

Key Takeaways:

ADCS misconfigurations can lead to complete domain compromise
Certificate forgery enables persistent, stealthy privilege escalation
Proper CA security and template configuration are essential
Regular audits of certificate templates and CA settings prevent exploitation
Defensive Recommendations:

Disable EDITF_ATTRIBUTESUBJECTALTNAME2 flag on CAs
Restrict certificate template enrollment permissions
Implement certificate transparency and monitoring
Require manager approval for sensitive certificate templates
Regularly audit certificate issuance logs
